make_unique_obj(string sFile)

  An lfun defined for all objects inheriting CLONE, which includes rooms
  and monsters. Attempts to create a unique object and move it to the
  calling object. Won't create an object if the object has already been
  created through make_unique_obj or clone_unique_object previously
  and such object is still in-game.

  Note: make_unique_obj returns 0 if the clone is unsuccessful.

  Example: 
           if(!make_unique_obj("/obj/uniq_sword"))
             make_obj("/obj/regular_sword");


See also: make_unique_and_equip, make_obj, make_limited_obj, 
          clone_unique_object
